24 Jul 2015 12:09






The only way this seems even somewhat interesting to me is in the context of the contest this was written for. It's a more clever way of having personnel deliberately minimizing the word count in-universe than most writers would probably come up with, in that the reasoning isn't the result of an anomaly that directly affects written language, but that's all it really has going for it, and even that is of debatable value.

If this was posted as a regular article without special rules and goals for the reader to have in mind before even reading it, I don't think the rating would be as fluctuant as it currently is, to put it one way.

I'm sorry, but the concept of transgressions unatonable by the standards of reality itself treads too close to concepts already attached to much more interesting SCPs. There's simply nothing here that could possibly make this stand out from the rest of the main list in a positive way.





